cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of denoising scanned documents using GANs. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as the focus is on image-to-image translation. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as CycleGAN and Conditional GAN, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL) research. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques such as OCR (Optical Character Recognition) for text recognition, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of unpaired image-to-image translation, which is a common problem in image retrieval (cs.IR).
